definition: to open up a path/to make one's way through/to construct a road/(electricity) open circuit

to open/to start/to turn on/to boil/to write out (a prescription, check, invoice etc)/to operate (a vehicle)/carat (gold)/abbr. for Kelvin, 開爾文|开尔文[Kai1 er3 wen2]/abbr. for 開本|开本[kai1 ben3], book format

sentences.english: The man went ahead of us to clear the course.
sentences.chinese: 这个人走在我们前头开路。

sentences.english: He'll guide you by putting his arm on your elbow or in the small of your back.
sentences.chinese: 他会用将手放在你手肘或者你的背部为你开路。

sentences.english: The Data and Clock lines are both open collector.
sentences.chinese: 数据和时钟线都是集电极开路的。

sentences.english: The ideal ammeter should read zero when its input terminals are left open.
sentences.chinese: 当输入端开路时，理想安培计的读数应当为零。

sentences.english: John was the forerunner to Jesus.
sentences.chinese: 施洗约翰是耶稣的开路先锋。

sentences.english: She elbowed her way through the masses of tourists.
sentences.chinese: 这个人走在我们前头开路。

sentences.english: On the other hand, at high cell temperature, OCV is higher with low feed of methanol concentration.
sentences.chinese: 在高温下，低浓度的甲醇进料拥有较高的开路电位。

sentences.english: Open-circuit signal line may be subject to interference arising from the incorrect output.
sentences.chinese: 开路的信号线可能会受到干扰而产生不正确的输出。

sentences.english: The author describes the techniques of open-loop vibrational control.
sentences.chinese: 作者介绍了开路振动控制技术。

sentences.english: The roadless difficult opening to be more difficult, therefore afterward artificial you sighed.
sentences.chinese: 无路难呀开路更难，所以后来人为你感叹。

sentences.english: The revolutionist is the trailblazer who moves the society forward.
sentences.chinese: 革命者是推动社会前进的开路先锋。

sentences.english: The old road has been blocked by bush. Need a big knife to cut through.
sentences.chinese: 古路已经被灌木封锁的了，要开山刀开路的了。

sentences.english: Kataoka himself cut the jungle by sword and made a route.
sentences.chinese: 片冈师团长亲自用刀开路。

sentences.english: Then came an earthmover to level off the ground for a fire engine.
sentences.chinese: 接著，推土机前来为消防车开路。

sentences.english: Thus saith the LORD, which maketh a way in the sea, and a path in the mighty waters;
sentences.chinese: 耶和华在沧海中开道，在大水中开路。

definition: to lead the way/to guide/to show the way/fig. to instruct
to bring up the rear/to provide support/to hold the lines
to guard/to protect/bodyguard (for officials in ancient times)
